2026-07-10T03:20:41.1824198Z             "body": "## Summary\nThis PR hardens the application with critical security controls, input validation, and cache persistence fixes. The main changes prevent accidental network exposure of unauthenticated instances, validate domain inputs, fix DNS cache timestamp handling, and improve error reporting.\n\n## Key Changes\n\n**Security & Access Control**\n- **Auth-disabled gating to localhost**: The server now refuses to start if authentication is disabled (`AuthTokenHash=none`) but bound to non-loopback addresses. Added `IsLoopbackOnlyBinding()` check that validates `ASPNETCORE_URLS`, `ASPNETCORE_HTTP_PORTS/HTTPS_PORTS`, and Kestrel endpoint configuration to ensure an open instance can only run locally.\n- **SSRF protection on debug endpoint**: The `/api/debug/proxy` endpoint now returns 404 when auth is disabled, preventing it from becoming an open SSRF surface on unauthenticated instances.\n- **Domain input validation**: Added `IsPlausibleDomain()` regex check on both validation endpoints to reject obvious bad/hostile inputs (userinfo `@`, path `/`, port `:`, whitespace, schemes) before they're interpolated into probe URLs.\n\n**HTTPS Certificate Validation**\n- Added `ValidateHttpsCertificates` configuration option (default `true`) to control TLS certificate validation on outbound HTTPS probes (MTA-STS, BIMI, DoH, security.txt, crt.sh).\n- When disabled, logs a warning that HTTPS verdicts cannot be trusted (only for TLS-intercepting proxies with untrusted CAs).\n- Updated `HttpProbeService` to conditionally set `ServerCertificateCustomValidationCallback` only when validation is disabled.\n\n**DNS Cache & Persistence**\n- **Per-entry fetch timestamps**: `ProbeCache<T>` now tracks when each value was fetched (`CachedAtUtc`), not just when it was cached. Added `ExportTimed()` and `Import(key, value, cachedAtUtc)` overloads to preserve real fetch times across disk save/load cycles.\n- **DNS response code persistence**: `DnsCacheEntry` now stores the DNS header RCODE (0=NoError, 3=NXDOMAIN, etc.). `CachedDnsResponse` reconstructs a minimal header from the persisted RCODE so consumers like `CheckContext.IsNxDomain` can read `Header.ResponseCode` from cached responses.\n- **LookupClient pooling**: `DnsResolverService` now reuses one `LookupClient` per target server IP (cached in `_serverClients`) instead of creating a fresh one per query, improving socket reuse and reducing allocations.\n\n**SPF Check Improvements**\n- **Exact \"all\" mechanism matching**: Changed from prefix match to exact equality check (`Equals(\"all\", ...)`) to correctly handle the bare \"all\" mechanism, which carries an implicit `+` qualifier per RFC 7208 §4.6.2.\n- **Qualifier normalization**: Explicitly extract and normalize the qualifier (`+`, `-`, `~`, `?`) from the \"all\" mechanism, treating bare \"all\" as `+all`.\n- **Severity based on errors/warnings**: SPF expansion result severity now reflects actual problems found — reports Error if any PermErrors occurred, Warning if warnings exist, Pass only if clean.\n- **Query error tracking fix**: SPF checks now read from `ctx.QueryErrors` (per-validation error bag via AsyncLocal) instead of `ctx.Dns.QueryErrors` (legacy CLI-only), correctly capturing transient DNS failures in web flows.\n\n**Job Cleanup & Stability**\n- Added hard cap (`_runningJobMaxAge = 2 hours`) for validation jobs stuck in Running state to prevent memory leaks from abandoned requests.\n- Updated cleanup logic to evict both finished jobs after retention window and stuck Running jobs after max age.\n\n**Token Security**\n- Removed `Hash` field from token issue response to avoid echoing the credential-equivalent verifier; the raw one-time token is the only secret callers need.\n- Updated documentation to emphasize minimum 128-bit entropy requirement for root tokens and the unsalted SHA-256 verification risk.\n\n**Documentation**\n- Updated `configuration.md` with\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01PD81wS9yngzumYcPpdYDsv",
